betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Your discovery of Void Metal made you wonder what would happen if you were to make an anvil out of it, after your earlier success doing the same with Thaumium.

The end result was unexpected, but a welcome surprise. Void Metal is able to retain its regenerating property even as an anvil. In addition, if an operation requires more than a certain amount of experience the anvil will instead use that experience to draw power from the void. Negating the need for more experience to finish the job.

If only your Forge Hammer machines could use this marvalous anvil. The sheer amount of punishment it can take would surely increase productivity compared to using even a Thaumium anvil.
